commit.message: Fixed issue with orders not being created and not being displayed
Fixed route for getting all of the orders belonging to a user
Configured react-router added routes for the front end
Added components to display all a users orders and a detailed view about a given order
Added routes to express app
Fixed naming of tables references in fulfills table
Added routes to interact with the order, supplier and user tables
Added utils to check that the user is logged in and to generate random integers
Added OrderForm which allows the user to create a new order
Created redux store and connected it to the app
Removed unnecessary styles
Added Navbar component
Created components to register, login and logout users
Added logo asset
Setup redux actions and reducers, created reducer to manage auth state
Added capitalizeString() util
Created typescript interfaces to model the database tables, as well as typealiases
Installed react-router for routing and redux for state management
Cleaned up auth routes file
Created express server
Added auth routes for handling authentication on the server
Removed extraneous property on user returned from passport strategy
Created passport-local strategy for authentication, created error handler middleware to catch errors
Created postgres pool to allow multiple connections to the database, added convenience function for easily querying the database, added sql script to create tables
Created typescript interfaces to model the database tables
Installed passport for auth, and pg for interacting with the database
Initial commit
